History[edit | edit source]
Announcement[edit | edit source]
@media screen and (max-width:1119px){.mw-parser-output th.vertical-header{min-width:1em}.mw-parser-output th.vertical-header>*{writing-mode:vertical-lr;transform:scale(-1);vertical-align:middle;line-height:1em}.mw-parser-output th.vertical-header div{display:inline-block;border:none;padding:0;margin:0}.mw-parser-output .historytable-experiment{margin:1em -4px 0.5em -4px}.mw-parser-output table[data-description="History"] th{line-height:1.2em}.mw-parser-output table[data-description="History"] th.nowrap{white-space:normal}.mw-parser-output table[data-description="History"] th:not(.historytable-subheader),.mw-parser-output .historytable-experiment+span{font-size:smaller}}September 29, 2018During MINECON Earth 2018, the Minecraft community voted on which biome to update next. The taiga biome was the most voted biome; therefore, foxes, campfires and sweet berries food sources and plants are to be added to the biome in Java Edition 1.14.[2]
Java Edition[edit | edit source]
Java Edition Alphav1.2.0previewAdded the snowy-covered taiga biomes along with many other biomes. However, the biome was fairly different to their modern counterpart. A notable difference was the use of oak trees as spruce and pine trees had yet to be added. All taigas were snowy and were defined by having a rainfall value of over 20% and a temperature value between 10% and 50%.Java Edition Beta1.2Spruce and pine trees now generate instead of oak trees.1.4Wolves were added and can now be found in the taigas.1.6Test Build 3Short grass can now generate.1.8Pre-releaseTaigas were reworked as part of the biome overhaul. The new terrain generator replaced the old version with a new taiga biome.Due to issues in the new terrain generator, taigas now generate without snow.Java Edition1.111w48aChanged the temperature value from 0.3 to 0.05, so taigas can again generate with snow layers.12w01aAdded the taiga hills biome as a variant with a hilly terrain.1.7.213w36aThe default taiga biome now generates without snow.
A fairly rare dedicated snowy taiga biome has been added.
Both types of taigas now generate with ferns and the new large fern.
Taiga is now required for the new "Adventuring Time" achievement.1.814w27aAdded rabbits, which spawn in taigas.1.1016w20aVillages made of spruce materials such as logs and planks now generate in the taiga biome.1.1418w47aAdded pillager outposts, which may generate in taiga biomes.18w49aAdded sweet berry bushes, which commonly generate in taiga biomes.19w07aAdded foxes, which spawn in taigas with a red fur texture.1.2023w12aAdded trail ruins, which can generate in taigas.23w17a"A Familiar Room" soundtrack can now be played in the taiga.1.21.525w02aPigs that spawn in taigas are now the cold variant.25w05aCows that spawn in taigas are now the cold variant.25w06aChickens that spawn in taigas are now the cold variant.
Bedrock Edition[edit | edit source]
Pocket Edition Alphav0.9.0build 1Added the separated snowless taiga and its variants with hills and mountains because older taigas were all snowy and had ice, along with a large number of other biomes.v0.13.0build 1Rabbits were added, they can spawn in taigas.v0.15.0build 1Villages built with spruce wood can now generate in taiga biomes. This used to be an exclusive game feature.Bedrock Edition1.10.0beta 1.10.0.3Added pillager outposts, which may generate in taiga biomes.
Added sweet berry bushes, which commonly generate in taigas.1.13.0beta 1.13.0.1Added foxes, which can spawn in taigas with a red tone of fur.1.21.60Preview 1.21.60.23Small ferns now generate more frequently.
Large ferns now generate less frequently.
Sweet berry bushes now generate in larger patches.1.21.60ExperimentDrop 1 2025Preview 1.21.60.25Pigs that spawn in taigas are now the cold variant.1.21.70ExperimentDrop 1 2025Preview 1.21.70.20Cows that spawn in taigas are now the cold variant.Preview 1.21.70.22Chickens that spawn in taigas are now the cold variant.1.21.90Preview 1.21.90.26Added semi-humid volumetric fog, cold lighting, and coolish color grading to taigas in Vibrant Visuals.
Legacy Console Edition[edit | edit source]
Legacy Console EditionXbox 360Xbox OnePS3PS4PS VitaWii USwitchTU1CU11.001.001.00Patch 11.0.1Added snow-covered taigas.TU9Added the taiga hills biome.TU31CU191.221.221.22Patch 3Added snowless taigas and their mountainous variants, along with many other biomes.   1.91   Added pillager outposts, which may generate in the taiga biomes.
Added sweet berry bushes, which commonly generate in taigas.
Data history[edit | edit source]
Java Edition1.1821w37aPrior to the removal of numerical biome IDs, this biome's numerical ID was 5.
Issues[edit | edit source]
Issues relating to "Taiga" are maintained on the bug tracker. Issues should be reported and viewed there.


